text: It's Jeff Barr here at AWS in Seattle.

Here's a couple of launches 
that caught my eye this week.

OpsWorks for Chef Automate now
 supports version one.eight.three,

which includes Chef’s 
infrastructure compliant scanner.

Now you can run Chef complaint scans, 
unknowns that are not managed by Chef,

giving you the ability 
to increase coverage.

Amazon Connect is now SOC compliant in 
all regions where the service is available.

If you need to connect, 
try it out through the AWS free tier.

Thanks for joining us this week
 for some of our launch highlights.

For the full state of recent launches, 
check out our What's New page.

Be sure like this video and subscribe, 
so you won’t  miss an update,
and we'll see you next time.
